A neighborhood Mexican restaurant.  Went here with a friend who comes here frequently.  The food is just average and overpriced for a Mexican restaurant. There are plenty of other places that are a lot better than this one.  Had the carne asada (broiled steak) with nopalitos (cactus)  It comes with rice, beans, a salad, and tortillas.  I expected skirt steak skirt steak, like you usually receive  Anna Mexican restaurant, but this meat tasted like a lower cut of meat.  The other meal that we tried was the chuletas de puerco (2 pork chops) with grilled onions. This also came with rice, beans, salad and tortillas.  The pork chops were paper thin and very unappetizing.  The third item that we ordered was a chicken pambazo, which is like a torta with chicken, beans, cheese, and salad inside.  Sadly it was lacking in all of these ingredients.  The best part of the meal was the handmade tortillas.  I cannot recommend this place and highly doubt that I will return.

Went looking for a burrito dinner for my last night in Albany Park (housesitting for a family member for 2 weeks) and this was one of few places within walking distance (blizzard outside) that had ground beef as an option. I also got a side of rice and beans to go (Blackhawks game on). They were EXTREMELY fast getting my food to me. They must be the Jimmy Johns of Mexican food. I get home and the burrito was so so. Very firm and not soggy. They skimp on the meat really badly. They mix it with potatoes too as filler I noticed on closer inspection. Most of it was lettuce and tomatoes. That kinda pissed me off.
